title: Koya Doras Keep Ancient Healing Traditions Alive At Medaram
description: The Koya Doras serve as a living bridge between modern pilgrims and the dense woodlands of the Srisailam and Medaram regions. They set up specialised stalls offering rare herbal remedies (vana moolikalu) collected from deep within the forests.
